                                        <comments>
                            <comment id="84722" author="david_syer" created="Wed, 31 Oct 2012 01:30:52 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Added some crude catch and log blocks, attempting to remove the offending row if possible.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="87603" author="phavelar" created="Mon, 4 Feb 2013 14:24:57 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi Dave,&lt;br/&gt;
These catch blocks are violating the Single Responsibility Principle. &lt;br/&gt;
The readAuthentication() and readRefreshToken() methods, are not read only operations. They can remove tokens in case of exceptions.&lt;br/&gt;
That is, one can no longer have it running under a read only transaction, because if there is an exception it will do a remove operation...  ideally they should only be read, and not cause a potential modification in the database.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="87758" author="david_syer" created="Fri, 8 Feb 2013 05:46:09 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Sorry, I don&apos;t see a way round that if you want to not fall over on mouldy tokens.  Please feel free to open more tickets (and propose fixes).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
